	id="Exa_Inverse22Matrix">
	<texsupport href="../LinearAlgebraTeXSupport.xml"/>
	
	<title>Inverse of a (2,2)-Matrix</title>
	
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>Find the inverse of the <latex>(2,2)</latex>-matrix</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
\Mtrx{A} = 
\left[
\begin{array}{rr}
3 & 4 \\
1 & 7
\end{array}
\right]
]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
			
			<para>provided it exists.</para>
		</statement>
		<answer type="Solution">
			<para>To test whether <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex> is invertible, we compute:</para>
			<computation>
				<left>\det(\Mtrx{A})</left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right>17 \neq 0</right>
			</computation>
			<para>Therefore <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex> is invertible. According to the formula for the inverse of an invertible  (2,2)-matrix, we find</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
\aligned
A^{-1}\ &=\ \frac{1}{\text{det}(A)}\,
\left[
\begin{array}{rr}
7 & -4 \\
-1 & 3
\end{array}\right] \\
   &=\ \frac{1}{17}\,
   \left[
\begin{array}{rr}
7 & -4 \\
-1 & 3
\end{array}\right]
\endaligned
]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
		</answer>
	</showme>
</showme.pack>